NAME

  **sleep** - sleep for <milliseconds> milliseconds

SYNOPSIS

    sleep *milliseconds*

DESCRIPTION

    The sleep command waits for *milliseconds* milliseconds, and then returns. While waiting,
    text inputs, mouse inputs and the like will be ignored. This will freeze any other processes
    running. If milliseconds is not a positive number, sleep will throw an error.

OPTIONS

    -h, --help:  output usage information and exit

SEE ALSO

    [splash](/data/man/splash.dsmd)